ZH: 今天早上发生了一起爆炸事件。
EN: There was an explosion this morning.

ZH: 爆炸发生在化学实验室里。
EN: The explosion happened in the chemistry lab.

ZH: 突然爆炸声吓了我一跳。
EN: The sudden explosion startled me.

ZH: 爆炸的声音震耳欲聋。
EN: The sound of the explosion was deafening.

ZH: 这次爆炸造成了很多人受伤。
EN: This explosion caused a lot of people to get injured.

ZH: 美国曾经发生过很多次炸弹爆炸事件。
EN: There have been many bomb explosions in the United States.

ZH: 消防队员及时赶到，成功扑灭了爆炸。
EN: The firefighters arrived on time and successfully extinguished the explosion.

ZH: 这座建筑因爆炸而倒塌。
EN: The building collapsed due to the explosion.

ZH: 据报道，这次爆炸是由气体泄漏引起的。
EN: According to reports, the explosion was caused by a gas leak.

ZH: 炸弹定时爆炸，造成大规模破坏。
EN: The timed bomb exploded, causing massive destruction.

ZH: 爆炸后，整个城市陷入了恐慌。
EN: The whole city was plunged into panic after the explosion.

ZH: 在爆炸中失去生命是一种悲剧。
EN: Losing lives in an explosion is a tragedy.

ZH: 希望这次爆炸不会有人员伤亡。
EN: Hopefully, there will be no casualties in this explosion.

ZH: 这次爆炸引发了大火，烧毁了周边建筑。
EN: The explosion triggered a massive fire, burning down nearby buildings.

ZH: 爆炸的威力超出了所有人的想象。
EN: The power of the explosion exceeded everyone's imagination.

ZH: 爆炸导致了城市供电中断。
EN: The explosion caused a city-wide power outage.

ZH: 事故调查显示，这次爆炸是由设备故障引起的。
EN: The accident investigation revealed that the explosion was caused by equipment failure.

ZH: 训练有素的消防员迅速控制住了爆炸现场。
EN: Well-trained firefighters quickly controlled the explosion site.

ZH: 爆炸之后，漆黑一片，看不见任何东西。
EN: After the explosion, it was pitch black and nothing could be seen.

ZH: 爆炸的冲击波摧毁了附近的建筑。
EN: The shockwave of the explosion destroyed nearby buildings.
